oing so, she concludes that adoption is an inadequate response to child welfare and on its own cannot solve problems regarding child neglect and abuse. Rather, Chambers argues that in order to reform the area of adoption we must first acknowledge that it is built upon social inequalities within and between nations.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aAdoptionxHistoryxOntarioxOntario. 0aAdoptionxLaw and legislationxHistoryxOntario. 0aAdoptionxLaw and legislationzOntarioxHistory. 0aAdoptionzOntarioxHistory. 7aHISTORY / Canada / General.2bisacsh1 aChambers, Lori, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311066595640uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148751226240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487512262423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781487512262.jpg  a978-3-11-066595-6  University of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles